subSubSection.paragraph:
Body wall of disc and arms a yellow sandy hue on upper and lateral surfaces. Colour of many spines and tubercles ranges from orange-red to pale pink with the orange-red pigmented spines forming a well-defined circular area centrally on the disc, then more diffuse areas peripherally towards the ends of the arms.Other spines and tubercles located between, or sometimes within, the orange-red zones are cream or pale pink (
Fig. 1A, B, F
). The large terminal superomarginal plates are orange to pink. Abactinal papulae are reddish. Actinal surface is sandy yellow to pale cream with broad, orange-yellow streaking along interradial zones and parallel but irregular minor streaks of the same colour at intervals along the arms (
Fig. 1C
).
